                <h1>Mastering Blurred Background Photography</h1>
                <p>Blurred background photography, or bokeh, emphasizes your subject by softening the backdrop. This technique, often used in portrait and product photography, creates a dreamy effect that draws attention to the focal point. Achieve stunning results by using a wide aperture, maintaining distance, and experimenting with depth of field.</p>
